06/12/2024 05:51;qm:65d20c5a-0c84-458e-8ce1-adb90d07460f:63c7fe80-ba74-445b-827f-3853911ab41d;{color:#172B4D}We distribute approximately 180 - 220 bags each week. Our bags contain the following items:{color} 
{color:#172B4D} Bottled water, milk shelf stable 8oz, juice box 6-10oz, applesauce cup 4oz, tuna pouch 2oz, package of peanut butter cracker (lance)/ chips 1oz bags variety, package of cookies/granola bar, cereal in prepackaged bowl, 2 saltine packs ( 2 cracker in each pack).{color}{color:#172B4D}{color}   

{color:#172B4D} I hope this helps. When I order it is based on need and the amount of storage space we have. Usually it is 50-60 cases of milk( 27 boxes per case), 12-18 cases of applesauce(96 cups per case), pallet or water ( 48 cases of 24 bottles per case). These items usually last 2- 3months.{color}{color:#172B4D}{color}  

{color:#172B4D} Items we get from Sckenck Foods include: 14 prepackaged cereal bowls (96 per case), 8 peanut butter cracker (12 8packs per case) , 20-30 juice boxes (motts 36 per case), 6 saltines (500 2pk) 8 cookies (120 pks per case). Trips to BJ's, Costco , Walmart and Amazon provide some of the above and also the 50 tuna (10-12 2oz pouches per box). Sometimes we even get Vienna sausages. Granted none of this is considered healthy but it is convenient and ready to eat.{color}{color:#172B4D}{color}{color:#172B4D}{color}  


{color:#172B4D} We also distribute canned goods to those who have a place to cook ( about 6-15) a week.{color}{color:#172B4D}{color}   

{color:#172B4D} Let me know if you have any questions or need anything else.{color}{color:#172B4D}{color} 
----

